stock horse
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a saddle horse used in handling sheep and cattle.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Also stock pony or stock mare; aka stockhorse, stock-horse, stock-pony, stock-mare.
